/s3/uploads/getty_images/1180491673/image_1180491673.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">Sundry Photography</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>My Thesis</h2> <p>After massive rallies delivered by the growth part of my portfolio, it became imbalanced as the share of defensive plays decreased in relative terms. Therefore, I am adding Johnson &amp; Johnson (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/JNJ\" title=\"Johnson &amp; Johnson\">JNJ</a></span>) stock to my portfolio and</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1180491673/image_1180491673.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4745229-johnson-and-johnson-dividend-legend-at-a-discount", "pub_date": "2024-12-19 19:00:00"}, {"id": "4745348", "title": "Middlesex Water: This Dividend King Is Not Worth Your Time", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://media.gettyimages.com/id/2160087422/photo/aerial-view-of-two-environmental-engineers-work-at-wastewater-treatment-plants-water.jpg?b=1&amp;s=612x612&amp;w=0&amp;k=20&amp;c=kD3Rdaauuhe82V0P1-w5zO4iXjHFq_YQlAkOYepE0Yg=\" alt=\"Aerial View of Two Environmental engineers work at wastewater treatment plants, Water management concept.\" data-id=\"2160087422\" data-type=\"getty-image\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">BugTiger/E+ via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>Legendary dividend stock <strong>Middlesex Water</strong> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MSEX\" title=\"Middlesex Water Company\">MSEX</a></span>) has been pummeled in recent weeks. The stock made a new relative high in early November, only to move from $70 to $55 in virtually a straight line. Does that make the</p>", "image": null, "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4745348-middlesex-water-this-dividend-king-is-not-worth-your-time", "pub_date": "2024-12-19 18:56:01"}]}